  "doc_id": "40017",
  "text": "Familiarity is the feeling of knowing about the behavior and the possibilities of an instrument. It can be associated with other concepts in the literature as mental model [CITATION_1] or as an extension of transparency [CITATION_2] . We believe that familiarity is a strong component of the live music experience as it provides the spectator the ability to detect the intentions and the virtuosity of the performance of the musicians as well as their errors. Several attempts have been made at improving the familiarity. In this section, we propose a quick review of these solutions and their limitations.",
